Types of Tabs

System Tabs

Permissions tab

  • There is system tab called Permissions, where you are able to see the current permissions on an object.
  • In the tab for all objects in the system are visible 4 sections: Special permissions, Inherited parent permissions, Inherited library permissions and Active permissions.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

Versions tab

  • There is system tab called Versions, so that you can easily see who and when has created a new version of the object.
  • In the tab in table form are listed all historical versions of the object
  • For each version is displayed: Link to the content of the version (compact header), the number of the version, the user who created the version, the time (date:time forma) when the version is created.
  • At the top of the table is displayed always the current version of the object.

 

 

Each other tabs are previously created by the user or are available according to defined tabs in the selected template.
